# Test Token System Endpoints
# Use this file with REST Client extension or similar tools

### 1. Get user balance (should create wallet if it doesn't exist)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/token/balance?userId=1

### 2. Add test tokens to user
POST http://localhost:5000/api/token/dev/add-test-tokens
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": 1,
  "amount": 100.00,
  "reason": "Initial test tokens"
}

### 3. Get wallet details
GET http://localhost:5000/api/token/wallet/1

### 4. Get transaction history
GET http://localhost:5000/api/token/transactions/1

### 5. Get system status
GET http://localhost:5000/api/token/system/status

### 6. Admin: Get dashboard
GET http://localhost:5000/api/admin/tokens/dashboard

### 7. Admin: Get all wallets
GET http://localhost:5000/api/admin/tokens/wallets

### 8. Admin: Adjust user balance (add tokens)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/admin/tokens/adjust-balance?adminUserId=1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": 1,
  "amount": 50.00,
  "reason": "Admin test credit"
}

### 9. Admin: Adjust user balance (remove tokens)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/admin/tokens/adjust-balance?adminUserId=1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": 1,
  "amount": -25.00,
  "reason": "Admin test debit"
}

### 10. Get updated transaction history
GET http://localhost:5000/api/token/transactions/1

### 11. Admin: Get all transactions
GET http://localhost:5000/api/admin/tokens/transactions

### 12. Admin: Get token statistics
GET http://localhost:5000/api/admin/tokens/statistics